### **3. Defining Prompts - Attributes and Signatures**

#### **Prompt Attribute:**
```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public sealed class McpServerPromptAttribute : Attribute
{
    /// <summary>Prompt name - defaults to method name if null</summary>
    public string? Name { get; set; }

    /// <summary>Human-readable title for display</summary>
    public string? Title { get; set; }

    /// <summary>Icon source URI (HTTP/HTTPS URL or base64 data URI)</summary>
    public string? IconSource { get; set; }
}
```

#### **Type-Level Marker (for whole-class scanning):**
```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Class)]
public sealed class McpServerPromptTypeAttribute : Attribute
{
    // Marker only - no properties
}
```

#### **Registering Prompts - Method Signatures:**

**Generic registration (recommended for Native AOT):**
```csharp
// Static and instance methods
public static IMcpServerBuilder WithPrompts<TPromptType>(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null)

// With instance target
public static IMcpServerBuilder WithPrompts<TPromptType>(
    this IMcpServerBuilder builder,
    TPromptType target,
    JsonSerializerOptions? serializerOptions = null)
```

**Direct registration:**
